  "prompt": "What should be my 12th board percentage to get admission in St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for B.Com?",
  "response": "St. Xavier's College (Autonomous), Mumbai, is known for its competitive admission process, especially for the Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) program. While specific percentage requirements can vary each year based on applicant pools and other factors, a general guideline is:\n\nTypically, a percentage of 85% or higher in your 12th board exams (especially from the Maharashtra State Board or equivalent) increases your chances of securing a spot. However, the cutoff may be higher in some years depending on the number of applicants and overall performances.\n\nTo get the most accurate and current information, I recommend checking the official St. Xavier's College website or contacting their admissions office directly, as they will provide the latest cutoff information and admission criteria for the current academic year.",
